 4. Scientific background and data 
 The way(s) of doing things presented in the previous section is used in this section to guess the risk 
 attitudes of individual farmers of the same age group 
 in southern Israel. Data were collected by the accounting office of Moshav Bin-Yahav. This cooperative settlement is located in the Arava area of 
 Israel. The Arava includes the plains between 
 the Red Sea and the Dead Sea. It is an dry area 
 with low minimum and high maximum temperatures, 
 making it an off-season producer of vegetables for 
 local and export markets. Other than a handful of 
 added/more settlements, the Arava area is poorly 
 populated. Each farm on the moshav is privately 
 controlled, and its money-based life depends on its 
 
 a money-making state. Output marketing and input buying 
 are done cooperatively because of scale advantages. 
 The moshav members accept the ways of thinking/basic truths/rules of selfemployment and back and forth/equal between people cooperation as their idea-based basis. The social behavioral normal behaviors in this 
 kind of settlement are very strict. New candidates 
 for membership have to meet these normal behaviors and the 
 majority of the members have to approve their entry. The strictness of these rules leads to a 
 (group of things that are all pretty much the same) population in terms of preferences. 
 Hence it is reasonable to think about  the differences in 
 preferences as a secondary (and differences in wealth 
 as the first (or most important)) factor affecting risk (point of view/way of behaving). 
 The data set has two parts. The first contains 
 (how money affects people's lives) (numbers that change/things that change) in the following order: care, care with money, management, experience, (husband or wife) work, 
 farming-based knowledge, (desire to do something/reason for doing something), land quality, education, and risk-looking (for) (point of view/way of behaving). These (numbers that change/things that change) 
 describing farmer (features/ qualities/ traits) were built by 
 means of a Delphi panel got together from among the 
 moshav leaders and farm advisors. The (numbers that change/things that change) are 
 rated from one to five and represent the agreement of 
 the panel. The higher the number, the better the 
 attribute, for example the better the management 
 ability, the higher the land quality, or the greater the 
 (related to a husband or wife) (thing that's given/work that's done). The second part of the data set 
 contains a thin slice time series sample on 101 
 farmers over 10 years (1973-1982). It contains grouped (numbers that change/things that change) consisting of total water use, total 
 water cost, and expense on other inputs such as 
 bug-killers, (material that makes plants grow better)s, and helping grow materials. The 
 dry conditions and the remoteness of any outside 
 water source make water the most critical input. 
 So, drip crop-watering/rinsing with water, a very (producing a lot with very little waste) way of using 
 water, is the most in control/most common technology. Disaggregated 
 data on (helped to grow) land, yield, and money/money income are available by crop for bell peppers, tomatoes, onions, 
 eggplant, and melons. Almost all farmers grow tomatoes, bell peppers and melons. A smaller number 
 also grow eggplant and onions. The accounting office, in most cases, does not record input expense 
 by crop, but it does record total input expense. 
 One can use a behavior expertic approach to recover the 
 input expense per crop (Just et al., 1990), and 
 then to recover the (money made/good thing received) for each crop per unit of 
 land. Two main factors cause the opportunity cost of 
 land to be zero. First, there is no market for land 
 because the land is owned by the government, and 
 
 z. 
 
 Bar-Shira et al. j Farming-based Money flow 17 ( 1997) 211-222 
 
 renting or selling it is illegal. Second, the land is 
 gave out to the farmer in (good) enough amount, such 
 that the self-employment way of thinking/basic truth/rule binds the time 
 restriction before the land restriction becomes binding. 
 
