 The decision process is based on (not definite) expectations of future (money made/good thing received), as well as on expected 
 variance of future (money made/good thing received). Future (money made/good thing received) expectations 
 are assumed to be based on previous years' (money made/good things received). 
 Since no farmer grows every crop every year some 
 values are missing. A farmer who has such missing 
 values is assumed to form perceptions of (money made/good thing received) for 
 those years based on farms which are just like 
 his jher own in terms of size, location, and owner 
 wealth. These missing values are guessed by moving backward (money made/good thing received) on year and farmer dummies. That is 
