 Finally, before going ahead to guess, we think about/believe possible difference/different version in risk (point of view/way of behaving) cross people. Following previous studies (Dillon and Scandizzo, 1978; Moscardi and de Janvry, 1977; Binswanger, 1980, 1981, 1982; Shahabuddin et al., 1986) 
 concerning bring outation of risk attitudes, we related 
 difference/different version in risk (point of view/way of behaving) to difference/different version in (how money affects people's lives) (features/ qualities/ traits) among people. Specifically, we replace the limit/guideline a in Eq. (21) by a 
 linear combination of the (features/ qualities/ traits). This allows 
 high levels of the measures of risk hatred of change/differ 
 across people but keeps the ability to stretch of total 
 risk disgust, 3{, constant. This way the guessed value 
 for f3 should be understood/explained as an guess of group ability to stretch. The extent to which the guess of 
 constant ability to stretch is believable depends on the scientific background. 
 
