 The guessed effects of farmer (features/ qualities/ traits) on 
 risk disgust are described/explained in the central part of Table 
 2. The most significant (features/ qualities/ traits) are care, 
 management, experience and education. Famously, 
 farmers with a higher level of experience as well as 
 farmers with better managerial abilities show a 
 lower degree of risk disgust. The gut feeling is simple. Risk is a complicating factor which farmers with 
 less experience or less managerial ability try to 
 avoid. Higher levels of education are related to 
 higher risk disgust, suggesting that educated farmers understand better how to avoid risk. Care is 
 also connected with higher risk disgust. A possible 
 explanation might be that farmers who work harder 
 can reduce ex-post risk and so appear (not wanting to do anything dangerous) 
 ex-ante. 
 The effects of farmer (features/ qualities/ traits) on the understood cost of labor (bottom part of Table 2) can be 
 divided into direct and indirect effects. The direct 
 effect is due to the hit/effect of the (features/ qualities/ traits) on 
 the time needed/demanded to help grow one unit of land. The 
 indirect effect comes through the tax rate of 
 substitution between fun and money. When less 
 time is loyal to/is dedicated to farm activities, more time is 
 loyal to fun so the tax rate of substitution 
 goes down. Because of this both effects work in the same 
 direction. Care, farming-based knowledge and, to a 
 lesser extent, education are expected to have positive 
 coefficients because they are likely to reduce the 
 time needed/demanded to help grow one unit of land. Care with money 
 should have a positive coefficient because money-saving 
 people tend to waste less time (or to save more 
 time). When land quality and labor are substitute 
 factors, the land quality is also expected to have a 
 positive coefficient. The cost of labor may increase 
 with management and experience: people who work 
 harder and longer may get higher produces and hence 
 be showed as having higher management ability and experience. 
