 in Figs. 1-3, (match up each pair of items in order). The middle-points of expected 
 and initial wealth are US$139,000 and US$107,000, 
 (match up each pair of items in order). These values are close to reality. The 
 middle-point coefficient of total risk disgust is 
 0.0000044. The middle-point coefficient of relative risk 
 disgust is 0.615. The middle-point coefficient of partial 
 risk disgust is 0.117. For comparison, Saha et al. 
 (1994) guessed the measure of relative risk disgust for Kansas wheat farmers to be 5.4 and Antle 
 ( 1987) guessed the measure of partial risk disgust 
 of Indian farmers to be in the range of 0.19 to 1.77. 
 Binswanger reported almost the same  results: his guessed 
 measure of partial risk disgust was between 0.32 
 and 1.72 for most of the people. Antle 
 (1989) re-confirmed his 1987 findings by reporting a 
 mean partial risk disgust of 1.11 for one village and 
 1.14 for the other. We find the measure of partial 
 risk hatred of be in the range of 0.04 to 0.52. So, 
 our sample of Israeli farmers shows a lower degree 
 of partial risk disgust than that of Indian farmers. 
 
