 7. Summary and ends/end results 
 This paper develops a way(s) of doing things to test the 
 effect of wealth changes on the measures of total, 
 relative, and partial risk disgust. The behavior of all 
 three measures were shown to be figured out by/decided by a 
 single limit/guideline, the ability to stretch of total risk disgust with respect to wealth. (related to/looking at/thinking about) Israeli farmers, our main findings were that the measure of 
 total risk disgust decreases with wealth, the 
 measure of relative risk disgust increases with 
 wealth, and the measure of partial risk disgust 
 increases in risky income and decreases with nonstochastic initial wealth. These studies suggest evidence supporting Arrow's guesses. 10 
 
